                <div class="tips-box" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                    <div class="tips-title">Quick Reference: The Four Standards</div>
                    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 15px; margin-top: 15px;">
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--psychomotor);">
                            <strong style="color: var(--psychomotor);">Standard 1:</strong> Develops a variety of motor skills
                        </div>
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #0f2044;">
                            <strong style="color: #0f2044;">Standard 2:</strong> Applies knowledge related to movement and fitness concepts
                        </div>
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--uncg-green);">
                            <strong style="color: #2d7a5f;">Standard 3:</strong> Develops social skills through movement
                        </div>
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #ffb71b;">
                            <strong style="color: #8b6914;">Standard 4:</strong> Develops personal skills, identifies personal benefits, and chooses to engage
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
